claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A flowchart outlining influenza vaccination dosing recommendations for children aged 6 months through 8 years for the 2022–23 season, based on prior vaccination history (yes or no/unknown) leading to either 1 or 2 doses administered ≥4 weeks apart, accompanied by surrounding text on vaccine timing and immunogenicity studies. does not support the claim because the figure presents pediatric dosing guidance and contains no information about Flublok or antigenic match with WHO- or FDA-selected strains
